      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OUR PREFERRED PAL (6) spotted them a big start last time out and could only manage to finish fifth over 1207m at this track (Dirt). Should camp just off the leaders. Will play a major role. FACTORY SETTING (5) was high in the betting on the back of some good lead-up form but disappointed when beaten 14 lengths into sixth at his last run 11 weeks ago over 1308m at this track (Dirt). Big chance to kick this campaign off with a win. LADY DELILAH (4) turned in a strong run last time when third at this track (Dirt) just eight days ago. Backing up quickly over the longer journey. Strong run last time and is among the winning hopes. NEW YORK SPECIAL (2) is a well-related three-year-old filly lining up for the first time. By Curlin from Achalaya who has produced some fine gallopers, including a winner at G1 level. Has fared well at the barrier draw and should be in the finish.",
